The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                A student of IIT Kharagpur was admitted to the Infectious Diseases Hospital in Beleghata with suspected swine flu on Monday. Saurav Verma had gone to the Kharagpur sub-divisional hospital with fever and cold. After learning that he had recently returned from Spain after completing a project, the doctors asked him to get himself admitted at ID hospital. Vermas throat and nasal swabs would be tested at the National Institute of Cholera and Enteric Diseases in the city on Tuesday.     Rashmani Koley, who looked after an elderly couple in their Gariahat flat, was arrested on Sunday for allegedly stealing gold ornaments and silver utensils worth around Rs 1 lakh while her employers were asleep. Ruchit Murarka told police his grandparents woke up in the afternoon on Saturday and discovered the theft. The cops questioned Koley and two helps. Koley allegedly broke down and confessed. The stolen items were seized from her home in South 24-Parganas, the police said.    Sanjay Mark Wadvanihas taken charge as the British deputy high commissioner for eastern India. He took over from Simon Wilson. Wadvani was born in Calcutta and his family moved to the UK in 1974.    The middle-aged woman whose partially decomposed body was found in the Maidan on Saturday was murdered at the spot from where her body was recovered, police said on Monday. An examination of the spot, behind a bush, revealed signs of struggle, said an officer of the detective departments homicide wing. This is the third murder in the area in the past four years.    The CPM has called a 12-hour Sonarpur bandh on Tuesday to protest the assault on party MLA Shyamal Naskar and three activists on Sunday night, allegedly by Trinamul supporters. Naskar and his supporters were allegedly assaulted in Chanditala while returning from a party meeting late on Sunday. On Monday, Asutosh Sarkar and Subrata Sarkar were arrested in this connection. Trinamul district leaders refuted the allegations.     Motorcyclist Debmalya Das, 28, and pillion rider Bhushan Das, 21, were critically injured after being hit by a taxi on the AJC Bose Road flyover on Sunday night. Police said the duo were admitted to National Medical College and Hospital. Taxi driver Mohammad Safi was arrested.                                                                                                                                                                   
